The Federal Capital Territory has announced that one coronavirus death has been recorded in Abuja. The FCTA disclosed this in a tweet via its Twitter account on Friday. The Administration also confirmed that 85 new cases of the viral infection have been recorded in the territory. The tweet reads ”85 NEW CASES, 1 DEATH IN THE FCT ”Summary of COVID19FCT as at July 2nd, 2020. ”Total number of confirmed cases: 2020. ”Total number of active cases: 1546. ”439 patients have been discharged with 35 deaths recorded. “Residents are urged to take preventive measures seriously.”